					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5997129#post-3815334</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5997129/joey-fucknuts-believes-in-himself#post-3815334</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 28 May 2018 01:40:40 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>tgjer</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1649421</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>One line that jumped out to me upon re-reading - this is when Joey finally confronts the scary Clouds:</p> <blockquote> <p>If they pulled some trick, and this was how his journey ended, then Joey would just fix himself and fly once more. <strong>He'd done it once and he could just keep doing it, again and again.</strong></p> </blockquote> <p>Joey flies directly into the dense wall of white magic he's terrified of, counting on the knowledge that <em>his journey had ended and he had fixed himself before</em>, and could do it again.</p> <p>Is this maybe a reference back to how Joey became the zombie we now know and love? In <em>Joey Fucknuts Builds a Flying Machine</em>, it's noted that Joey had seen writing utensils before, but had forgotten about them after his death. So it sounds like maybe at one point he was a non-anomalous living human. Then his journey ended, but he refused to accept that ending, he still had shit to do, so he fixed himself and kept going.</p> <p>I'm hoping this is foreshadowing for Joey fixing himself after blasting the ambiguously existing hell hound out of existence. His journey isn't over yet, he hasn't finished accomplishing whatever it is the Boss set him out to do! To learn about the world, to bring stories back to his friends, to bring them to the light!</p> <p>Joey can't be really dead. He still has shit to do. He'll fix himself.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
